For purposes of appeal to the Court of Appeals, it is an alternative to a transcript of the proceeding as a record of the facts, testimony and other incidents of trial so that the Court of Appeals can be informed of those matters at trial which are now important in the appeal of the case. 

Source:[VA Circuit Court Civil Glossary](http://www.courts.state.va.us/courts/circuit/resources/manuals/cc_manual_civil/glossary.pdf)